171
00:08:13,315 --> 00:08:13,798


172
00:08:13,798 --> 00:08:15,021
Who is that?

173
00:08:15,021 --> 00:08:16,064


174
00:08:16,064 --> 00:08:17,450
It's my Dad.
Excuse me.

175
00:08:17,450 --> 00:08:44,029


176
00:08:44,029 --> 00:08:46,327
Please take care of yourself

177
00:08:46,327 --> 00:08:46,926


178
00:08:46,926 --> 00:08:47,965
Thank you

179
00:08:47,965 --> 00:08:58,950


180
00:08:58,950 --> 00:09:03,950
Kekkon Dekinai Otoko

181
00:09:03,950 --> 00:09:04,950


182
00:09:04,950 --> 00:09:07,950
Translation: InCyphe (-.,-);

183
00:09:07,950 --> 00:10:39,049


184
00:10:53,349 --> 00:10:55,906


185
00:10:55,906 --> 00:10:58,163
You put in the desired budget this morning right?

186
00:10:58,163 --> 00:10:58,886
Yes

187
00:10:58,886 --> 00:11:01,985
They decided to have separate entrances

188
00:11:01,985 --> 00:11:02,867


189
00:11:02,867 --> 00:11:06,091
I don't know what to do...

190
00:11:06,091 --> 00:11:16,014


191
00:11:16,014 --> 00:11:17,823
Kaneda updated his site

192
00:11:17,823 --> 00:11:24,089


193
00:11:24,089 --> 00:11:28,174
At the bar I frequent
I tried a new cocktail

194
00:11:28,174 --> 00:11:30,202
As usual, goofing around and not working

195
00:11:30,202 --> 00:11:31,917
I guess he's got nothing to worry about

196
00:11:31,917 --> 00:11:32,483


197
00:11:32,483 --> 00:11:33,767
I'm going to the bathroom

198
00:11:33,767 --> 00:11:39,144


199
00:11:39,144 --> 00:11:40,779
Kaneda-san's homepage?

200
00:11:40,779 --> 00:11:41,349
Yup

201
00:11:41,349 --> 00:11:42,473
I'm looking at it now

202
00:11:42,473 --> 00:11:44,565
You see the lady's hand in the photo?

203
00:11:44,565 --> 00:11:49,276


204
00:11:49,276 --> 00:11:50,486
Eh?

205
00:11:50,486 --> 00:11:52,183
That bracelet...

206
00:11:52,183 --> 00:11:54,049


207
00:11:54,049 --> 00:11:55,423
What are you looking at?

208
00:11:55,423 --> 00:12:04,232


209
00:12:04,232 --> 00:12:05,636
Mmm...

210
00:12:05,636 --> 00:12:08,644
We only met once!

211
00:12:08,644 --> 00:12:10,798
I don't care if it is Kaneda

212
00:12:10,798 --> 00:12:14,321
I'm more curious why you didn't tell me about it

213
00:12:14,321 --> 00:12:16,111
Well let's drop this now

214
00:12:16,111 --> 00:12:19,253
You're the one who ratted me out!

215
00:12:19,253 --> 00:12:19,987
Hey

216
00:12:19,987 --> 00:12:22,042
Can I ask you something?

217
00:12:22,042 --> 00:12:22,875


218
00:12:22,875 --> 00:12:23,785
This guy...

219
00:12:23,785 --> 00:12:27,467
said he won't live with my parents if we get married

220
00:12:27,467 --> 00:12:29,393
Wha.. you guy's are getting married?

221
00:12:29,393 --> 00:12:30,345
No

222
00:12:30,345 --> 00:12:32,987
What's the point of this if we're not marrying?

223
00:12:32,987 --> 00:12:35,978
Marrying, not marrying is not the point.
It's the way you think.

224
00:12:35,978 --> 00:12:37,569
I'm a bit surprised by it

225
00:12:37,569 --> 00:12:38,595
Me too

226
00:12:38,595 --> 00:12:43,329
If my boyfriend told me he doesn't want to live with my parents
that would be depressing

227
00:12:43,329 --> 00:12:44,308
Let me ask this

228
00:12:44,308 --> 00:12:46,832
Are you willing to live with your husband's Mom?

229
00:12:46,832 --> 00:12:47,890
I pass~

230
00:12:47,890 --> 00:12:50,216
I don't want to get nagged by Mother in-law

231
00:12:50,216 --> 00:12:51,291
It depends on the person

232
00:12:51,291 --> 00:12:53,448
If my husband-to-be is a proper person,

233
00:12:53,448 --> 00:12:56,438
then his mother has to be one too, no?

234
00:12:56,438 --> 00:12:58,738
I don't see any problem living together in that case

235
00:12:58,738 --> 00:12:59,977
Well said~

236
00:12:59,977 --> 00:13:01,624
You're talking about ideal

237
00:13:01,624 --> 00:13:04,980
Who cares~  It's not going to happen for awhile anyway

238
00:13:04,980 --> 00:13:20,697


239
00:13:20,697 --> 00:13:21,359
Excuse me

240
00:13:21,359 --> 00:13:38,519


241
00:13:38,519 --> 00:13:39,381
Sorry

242
00:13:39,381 --> 00:13:40,315


243
00:13:40,315 --> 00:13:41,234
This too

244
00:13:41,234 --> 00:14:11,126


245
00:14:11,126 --> 00:14:13,003
What's going on?

246
00:14:13,003 --> 00:14:14,067
Sorry,

247
00:14:14,067 --> 00:14:16,710
Don't ask why, but can I stay here tonight?

248
00:14:16,710 --> 00:14:17,165


249
00:14:17,165 --> 00:14:19,040
Sure you can but...

250
00:14:19,040 --> 00:14:23,206


251
00:14:23,206 --> 00:14:26,488
Why are you avoiding your father?

252
00:14:26,488 --> 00:14:29,451
He probably wants me to go on omiai (date)

253
00:14:29,451 --> 00:14:35,309
He says it looks bad to stay single past 35
so he's always nagging

254
00:14:35,309 --> 00:14:37,905
So why not just go on omiai?

255
00:14:37,905 --> 00:14:41,060
I want to go on one too...

256
00:14:41,060 --> 00:14:44,149
I never liked any news father came to tell me

257
00:14:44,149 --> 00:14:48,848
Saying stuff like how sincerity is the sole best quality,

258
00:14:48,848 --> 00:14:49,356
and...

259
00:14:49,356 --> 00:14:53,812
that wives should be stay-at-home Mom

260
00:14:53,812 --> 00:14:55,904
Must have old view of marriage

261
00:14:55,904 --> 00:14:58,966
He says how a relative gave birth to two kids,

262
00:14:58,966 --> 00:15:02,996
and how that's being a better daughter to him

263
00:15:02,996 --> 00:15:06,643
Well all parents say stuff like that

264
00:15:06,643 --> 00:15:09,445
My Mom passed away 3 years ago

265
00:15:09,445 --> 00:15:11,038
Really?

266
00:15:11,038 --> 00:15:16,545
Since losing her, he has become more stubborn and nosy

267
00:15:16,545 --> 00:15:40,700


268
00:15:40,700 --> 00:15:41,352
Ah

269
00:15:41,352 --> 00:15:43,158


270
00:15:43,158 --> 00:15:46,839
-Ah, from the hospital....
-No, you're mistaken

271
00:15:46,839 --> 00:15:48,208
No, it's you!

272
00:15:48,208 --> 00:15:49,583


273
00:15:49,583 --> 00:15:51,406
Ah.. yeah yeah...

274
00:15:51,406 --> 00:15:52,096


275
00:15:52,096 --> 00:15:54,168
You shouldn't drink alcohol

276
00:15:54,168 --> 00:15:55,843


277
00:15:55,843 --> 00:15:57,193
Why do you say that...

278
00:15:57,193 --> 00:15:57,964


279
00:15:57,964 --> 00:15:59,872
You have an illness

280
00:15:59,872 --> 00:16:00,358


281
00:16:00,358 --> 00:16:01,228
Ah~

282
00:16:01,228 --> 00:16:04,544
I don't mean to be nosy
but what illness do you have?

283
00:16:04,544 --> 00:16:05,949
It's none of your business

284
00:16:05,949 --> 00:16:07,290
It's not

285
00:16:07,290 --> 00:16:11,936
But I can't let a sick person drink

286
00:16:11,936 --> 00:16:34,031


287
00:16:34,031 --> 00:16:37,054
- Do you need a spoon?
- No

288
00:16:37,054 --> 00:16:38,615
- Do you have a point card?
- No

289
00:16:38,615 --> 00:16:51,567


290
00:16:51,567 --> 00:16:52,593
Eh?

291
00:16:52,593 --> 00:16:56,307


292
00:16:56,307 --> 00:16:58,627
I'll just tell you the truth

293
00:16:58,627 --> 00:16:59,654
You know,

294
00:16:59,654 --> 00:17:01,768
I was in the hopsital for just summer fatigue,

295
00:17:01,768 --> 00:17:03,875
and ran into your daughter,

296
00:17:03,875 --> 00:17:07,034
and just went along with her story

297
00:17:07,034 --> 00:17:07,619


